#N BirthOnSix
#C Exercises the variant-only rule. The centre cell (1,1) is dead but has exactly
#C 6 live neighbours, so it MUST come alive next generation. Under vanilla Conway
#C (birth only on 3) it would stay dead — this is the case that catches a missing
#C "birth on 6".
x = 3, y = 3, rule = B36/S23
3o$obo$o!
